---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Cai" noIndex={true}>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">Terms of Service</h1>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. About Cai</h2>
        <p>
          Cai is free, open-source software distributed under the
          <a href="https://github.com/clipboard-ai/cai/blob/main/LICENSE" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MIT License</a>.
          The source code is publicly available on <a href="https://github.com/clipboard-ai/cai" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
          By downloading, installing, or using Cai, you agree to these terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Open Source License</h2>
        <p>
          Cai is provided under the MIT License. You are free to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute,
          sublicense, and/or sell copies of the software, subject to the conditions of the MIT License.
          The full license text is included with the software and available in the
          <a href="https://github.com/clipboard-ai/cai/blob/main/LICENSE" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">project repository</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. Disclaimer of Warranty</h2>
        <p>
          Cai is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to
          the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and noninfringement. The entire risk
          as to the quality and performance of the software is with you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          In no event shall the authors or copyright holders be liable for any claim, damages, or other liability,
          whether in an action of contract, tort, or otherwise, arising from, out of, or in connection with the
          software or the use or other dealings in the software.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. AI Providers and Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          By default, Cai processes everything locally on your Mac using a built-in model or a local AI server
          (such as LM Studio or Ollama). You may choose to connect to cloud AI providers by configuring your local
          model server to proxy requests, or by entering a cloud API key directly in Cai's settings. If you use a
          cloud provider, your selected text is transmitted to that service for processing.
          You are solely responsible for your use of these third-party services and for complying with their respective
          terms of service and privacy policies. Cai does not control and is not responsible for the output generated
          by any AI model.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. User Responsibility</h2>
        <p>
          You are responsible for how you use Cai and any content processed through it. Do not use Cai for any
          purpose that is unlawful or prohibited by these terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cai allows advanced users to create custom output destinations that execute shell commands and AppleScript
          on your Mac. These scripts run with your user-level permissions and can perform any action your account
          is allowed to perform — including modifying or deleting files, sending network requests, and controlling
          other applications. You are solely responsible for any scripts or commands you configure. The authors of
          Cai are not liable for any damage, data loss, or unintended consequences resulting from user-created
          scripts or destinations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Website</h2>
        <p>
          This website (getcai.app) is provided for informational purposes. We strive to keep the information accurate
          and up to date, but make no guarantees about the completeness or accuracy of the content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.
          Continued use of Cai after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Applicable Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These terms shall be governed by the laws of the Federal Republic of Germany. If you are a consumer
          residing in the European Union, you also enjoy the protection of the mandatory provisions of the law
          of your country of residence.
        </p>
        <p>
          You have the right to file a claim through the European Commission's online dispute resolution platform at
          <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these terms is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions
          shall continue in full force and effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these terms, please contact us at:<br />
          Email: <span id="email-address"></span>
        </p>
      </section>

      <script>
        const user = "web";
        const domain = "getcai.app";
        const element = document.getElementById("email-address");
        if (element) {
          element.innerHTML = `<a href="mailto:${user}@${domain}" class="link">${user}@${domain}</a>`;
        }
      </script>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0A0A0A 0%, #111111 100%);
    padding: 10rem 0 6rem;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--gradient-start) 0%, var(--gradient-end) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal-section p {
    color: #B0B0B0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    color: #B0B0B0;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .link {
    color: var(--accent-light);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-pink);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: #808080;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-page {
      padding: 7rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .page-title {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .legal-section p,
    .legal-section ul {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
